    >[x] add plan_path to config $SLICE 1 — config key only, nothing reads it yet. default directory all plans are written to as flat <plan_path>/<charter>/<uid>.ics; projects inherit the default unless they override locally. server owns the calendar collection (.Radicale.props); we only write .ics into it. lands in config.schema.json + configuration.md, the core WorkspaceConfig struct, and each tool's config loading. path-threading is SLICE 2 (see export/import action + README Wiring)$ +specifications,library %2026-06-29T20:08 #019f027b-fa30-7701-8920-7592cb9fb943
    >[x] add git-ignored config.local.json layer $personal per-developer override of a committed project config — slots between .clearhead/config.json and env in load_config precedence (global → project → project.local → env → args). landed: load_config adds the local source after project config; clearhead init writes a scoped .clearhead/.gitignore (config.local.json) before its config-exists guard so existing workspaces pick it up on rerun; debug surfaces project_local_config_file + resolved plan_path; configuration.md documents the full ladder (previously omitted both project layers). verified e2e: plan_path resolves project → local → env in order$ +specifications,cli %2026-06-29T20:08 #019f12e0-2490-723a-875e-187dae2663b1
    >[x] export/import/archive read ONLY .ics under plan_path $SLICE 2 — landed & verified. REVISED the recorded design after reading the caller graph: resolve_workspace_layout is left UNTOUCHED (10 callers, only 2 on the plan path — threading it would make 7 config-blind callers pass None and centralize nothing). Instead the override rides a narrow _with_plans family (load_domain_model_with_plans/Workspace::load_with_plans/load_workspace_with_plans/collect_plan_files_with_plans) over a new pub(crate) leaf collect_plan_files_in(plans_root, project_root_charter); plain fns delegate with None so archive/manifest/graph/save-tests/lsp keep default behavior (no boilerplate). load_workspaces applies config.plan_path to the PRIMARY only. CLI contains it in CommandContext::{plan_override,load_model,load_charters,collect_plan_files,plans_root}; every primary-load call site routes through those. read/expand/plan-archive/export/import/add-plan all honor plan_path (proven e2e: default→empty-when-moved→found-via-override, through both env and config.local.json). GAP by design: charter-level archive (core archive_charter moving a whole charter's plans_dir) still uses default — its handling of server-owned .ics belongs with the next action. never read the caldav server's own sidecar json (radicale's) — server-implementation state, not the shared contract. the server owns the files; we own the actions$ +cli,library %2026-06-29T20:08 #019f027d-cafc-7a51-839c-04bdcc615afd
    >[x] only remove ABSENT ics, never touch present ones $ARCHIVE HALF LANDED. archive_charter no longer touches .ics at all: removed the remove_dir_all(plans_dir) that destroyed server-owned files, dropped plans from the archived DomainModel (actions already carry scheduled_at/due_at — the .ics is a redundant calendar projection), and removed the now-meaningless plans_swept field (struct + both CLI report sites). archive never needs plan_path threaded as a result — the slice-2 charter-archive gap closes by deletion, not plumbing. CONSEQUENCE accepted as honest: a charter whose .ics outlive it resurfaces as an implicit charter on next load (loader synthesizes one, load.rs:329) — reflects that the calendar still holds those events until the user clears them. spec updated (workspace.md Archival §: .ics explicitly NOT archived/deleted). regression test archive_leaves_ics_in_place locks it in. archive was the ONLY extant code that touched present .ics (no .ics-write path exists yet); the same never-touch-present / overwrite-only-on-change discipline on the FUTURE generate side is now carried as a constraint on the reconcile action below$ +specifications,library %2026-06-29T20:08 #019f0284-4096-7943-b065-0ddae837ca4d
    >[x] add scheduled_at_sync / due_date_sync action properties $the B column — merge base for the three-way sync. REVISED PLACEMENT: SIDECAR, not DSL (charter said DSL). B is machine-owned bookkeeping ('B drifting is a bug') with no user intent; the codebase already routes exactly this kind of field (created, source_vevent — the other CalDAV-linkage half) through ActMeta in .<charter>.json, hydrated onto Action. So: two Option<DateTime<Local>> on ActMeta (scheduled_at_sync/due_date_sync, skip_serializing_if None) + mirror fields on domain Action (Default None) + hydrate_acts assigns them directly (no DSL source). NAMING: due_DATE_sync to mirror the actual field domain::Action.due_date (charter's due_at_sync was aspirational; due_date is the real field). ZERO tree-sitter grammar work. spec: charter_metadata.schema.json documents both B fields (machine-owned, absent='never synced'); workspace.md prose already defers to the schema. README Syncing-state § corrected to sidecar placement + due_date_sync + the None='never synced' / stamped-atomically-with-.ics note. tests: B roundtrips through sidecar JSON + hydrates onto Action; RON snapshots regenerated (only the 2 new None fields added per action). DEFERRED to the reconcile engine (agreed): graph triples for B, and the write-back that actually MOVES B (stamped in the same write as C/.ics)$ +specifications,library %2026-07-10T07:41 #019f12da-3161-778f-bc2f-5bf7b9dda3f4
    >[x] implement the three-way reconcile (A/B/C table) $LANDED end-to-end across core + cli. The pure decision layer remains in core reconcile.rs: reconcile(A,B,C) -> Reconcile{NoOp|TakeAction|TakeCalendar|Converged|Conflict}, with the changed/changed refinement that A==C is Converged, not conflict. The shell is now landed too: (1) mirror-path policy moved out of cli plan.rs into clearhead-core workspace::calendar (shared charter dir policy, reserved next, plans_dir override, <uid>.ics naming); (2) apply_sync(root, plan_override, report) in core applies reports with the charter's required ordering — TakeAction writes the .ics FIRST then stamps B, TakeCalendar stages .actions + sidecar in ONE PendingBatch, Converged stamps B only, Conflict surfaces + skips; (3) cli gained a thin `clearhead sync calendar` command where plan_sync drives --dry-run and apply_sync drives apply, explicitly separate from telemetry-backfill `sync events`. Verified with core tests plus cli integration coverage for push-to-calendar and pull-from-calendar paths. SCOPED (still intentionally) to scheduled_at/DTSTART only; due_date_sync remains dormant until/if VTODO enters scope.$ +cli,library %2026-07-10T07:41 #019f12d4-4f7c-7bc2-9c76-b048067d43e8
    >[x] conflict-merge for the four conflict rows $LANDED as explicit user-directed resolution on `clearhead sync calendar --conflict <action|calendar>`. Conflicts still surface and skip by default; nothing is silently chosen. When the user opts in, every Conflict row is rewritten to the corresponding TakeAction/TakeCalendar outcome, which covers both changed-vs-changed and changed-vs-removal with the same source-of-truth choice. Dry-run shows the resolved push/pull plan; apply runs through the same ordered write shell already built for non-conflict outcomes. CLI integration tests cover both `--conflict action` and `--conflict calendar`.$ +cli,library %2026-07-10T07:41 #019f121e-1690-713d-bc14-ab564ea38179
    >[x] treat B changed/removed as a BUG $LANDED as loud surfacing in the sync planner rather than silent normalization. SyncReport now carries warnings, and plan_sync emits them for the suspicious B-drift shapes we can actually observe from A/B/C without extra provenance: (1) B missing while a calendar mirror already exists, and (2) A and C already agree while B differs (the classic stale/corrupted merge-base shape, also the crash-recovery shape). CLI `sync calendar` prints those warnings to stderr before listing actions, so users get guidance instead of the run quietly looking like an ordinary edit. We still self-heal via Converged/apply_sync, but no longer invisibly. Covered by reconcile shell tests.$ +cli,library %2026-07-10T07:41 #019f12b8-fa9e-7b2f-8875-19a9c17054b4
